fr:title.text: Composites in a quasicategory are unique up to equivalence

fr:frontmatter.fr:title: Composites in a quasicategory are unique up to equivalence

fr:mainmatter.fr:p: Let x\xrightarrow {f} y, y\xrightarrow {g} z, and x\xrightarrow {h,h'} z be morphisms in a quasicategory so that h\overset {\sigma }{\simeq }g\circ f and h'\overset {\sigma '}{\simeq } g\circ f. Then there is an equivalence h\simeq h'.
